verbose_text: XREF_BIBR The Phe55 residue could also be critical for protein stability; this possibility is exemplified by a pathogenic variant involving another member of the Cx 9 C family, COA6, in which a pathogenic mutation involving the conserved aromatic Trp59 residue was shown to cause COA6 protein instability.
